                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/2810</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Guayaquil</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_GFW1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Goding</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guayaquil</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-08-09T15:00:00-05:14">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 9, 1916, 3 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 9.20 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I have been notified, by Grace and Company all their steamers refuse to carry
                    cargo belonging black-list Americans as well as others to any port. Shall I
                    refuse bills health?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GFW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Goding</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
